race.description: Jarrod Arentz Electrical & Solar Solutions Mdn Plate
race.comment: FAERIE (5) only faded late first up at Echuca when firmly in the market over 1000m, beaten 2.5 lengths into fourth with improvement to come. Should improve going to 1200m now and her profile suggests she'll take a power of beating. JELLY BEAR (12) ran well on debut at Echuca over this distance when a narrow fourth. Open to plenty of improvement, she'll just need some luck in running from a wide gate. DANCE LADY (11) was well beaten on debut before a spell at Geelong. It wouldn't shock if she improved having placed in a recent jump out. PACIFIC PARADISE (13) is a filly by North Pacific on debut for the Alexander yard, watch the betting in a winnable maiden. SARAYA (7) has had plenty of chances but is going well and can threaten.
